                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13246423" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 4 Apr 2012 16:19:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that since the cli has behaved this way since 1.0.0, changing it now might surprise people who didn&apos;t read NEWS (and thus don&apos;t know that it was supposed to change to default of 0.1).  So I propose fixing this in 1.1.0 instead. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(For completeness, I note that cql &lt;tt&gt;CREATE COLUMNFAMILY&lt;/tt&gt; does default to 0.1 correctly since it does not build its CFMetadata objects from Thrift.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13246449" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 4 Apr 2012 16:38:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 and tested by creating a cf via cli. (  and read_repair_chance = 0.1 )&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
